EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to accountants; revising the requirements for the
granting of a certificate of certified public accountant;
requiring the Nevada State Board of Accountancy to
prescribe by regulation certain requirements and standards
for the issuance of a certificate of certified public
accountant; revising provisions governing certain fees that
the Board is authorized or required to charge; revising
provisions governing the examination required for the
issuance of a certificate of certified public accountant; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides for the regulation of accountants in this State by the
2 Nevada State Board of Accountancy. (Chapter 628 of NRS)
3 Existing law sets forth certain requirements relating to the education and work
4 experience required for a person to be issued a certificate of certified public
5 accountant. (NRS 628.200) Section 2 of this bill eliminates those requirements and
6 instead requires the Board to prescribe by regulation the requirements and standards
7 for education and work experience which the Board deems appropriate for the
8 issuance of a certificate of certified public accountant. Section 2 sets forth certain
9 requirements for those regulations. Section 5 of this bill makes a conforming
10 change to reflect the elimination of the requirements for education and work
11 experience in section 2 and the authority of the Board to adopt such requirements
12 by regulation.
13 With certain exceptions, existing law requires the Board to grant a certificate of
14 certified public accountant to a person who satisfies certain requirements for
15 education, work experience and passing an examination as set forth in statute.
16 (NRS 628.190) Section 1 of this bill revises these provisions to require the Board,
17 with certain exceptions, to grant such a certificate to a person who: (1) complies
-
