18 with the requirements and standards of education and work experience prescribed
19 in regulations adopted by the Board; and (2) has passed all sections of the
20 examination prescribed by the Board in accordance with the terms and conditions
21 prescribed in any regulations adopted by the Board. Section 1 also provides that an
22 applicant for such a certificate is subject to the educational requirements to receive
23 a certificate that were in effect on the date on which the applicant passed all
24 sections of the examination prescribed in the regulations of the Board.
25 Existing law authorizes the Board to establish a fee for the evaluation of the
26 experience of a candidate for a certificate of certified public accountant. (NRS
27 628.250) Section 3 of this bill eliminates the authority of the Board to establish
28 such a fee.
29 Existing law authorizes the Board to prescribe by regulation the terms and
30 conditions under which a candidate for a certificate of certified public accountant:
31 (1) may receive conditional credit for passing at least one section, but not all
32 sections, of the examination required to qualify for the certificate; and (2) need not
33 sit for reexamination in sections which the candidate has passed and for which he
34 or she has received conditional credit. Existing law also authorizes the Board to
35 provide by regulation a limit on the time in which a candidate must pass all sections
36 of the examination or lose any credit received. (NRS 628.260) Section 4 of this bill
37 clarifies the authority of the Board with respect to the establishment of terms and
38 conditions concerning the passage of the required examination by specifying that
39 the regulations of the Board may, but are not required, to: (1) authorize a candidate
40 who has not passed all sections of the examination to receive credit for any section
41 of the examination passed without being required to sit for reexamination of those
42 sections; and (2) provide a limit on the time in which a candidate must pass all
43 sections of the examination or lose any such credit received.
44 Existing law requires the Board to adopt regulations that prescribe a fee for
45 registering a fictitious name with the Board. (NRS 628.375) Section 6 of this bill
46 removes this requirement and instead authorizes the Board to establish such a fee.
